%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Falivus-life-q3-results-net-profit-rises-to-rs-137-cr-revenue-jumps-12-125012300784_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22CEOs%20have%20a%20new%20skill%20to%20learn%3A%20managing%20AI%20employees%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224510%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lattice%20CEO%20Sarah%20Franklin%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F679210ea2fcded5e907463ba%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222653%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESarah%20Franklin%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Lattice%2C%20previously%20tried%20giving%20AI%20workers%20employment%20records.%20%3Cp%3ECarlos%20Rodrigues%2FSportsfile%20for%20Web%20Summit%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-is-agentic-ai-agents-2024-12%5C%22%20data-autoaffiliated%3D%5C%22false%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAgentic%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20makes%20decisions%20without%20human%20input%2C%20is%20a%20hot%20topic%20at%20Davos%20this%20year.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAI%20agents%20promise%20tangible%20benefits%20to%20companies%20but%20raise%20questions%20such%20as%20whether%20they%20should%20get%20KPIs.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBusiness%20leaders%20now%20have%20to%20work%20out%20how%20to%20manage%20autonomous%20bots%20alongside%20human%20employees.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20companies%20are%20using%20AI%20to%20get%20better%2C%20faster%2C%20and%20leaner%20%E2%80%94%20but%20what%20happens%20when%20artificial%20intelligence%20is%20not%20just%20your%20tool%20but%20your%20colleague%20or%20your%20employee%3F%20Should%20it%20be%20trained%20like%20a%20human%2C%20given%20goals%20and%20performance%20metrics%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20reality%20setting%20in%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdavos-world-economic-forum-day-three-diary-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWorld%20Economic%20Forum%20in%20Davos%3C%2Fa%3E%20this%20year%3A%20business%20leaders%20will%20soon%20have%20to%20decide%20how%20to%20manage%20not%20only%20their%20human%20workforce%20but%20also%20a%20new%20class%20of%20AI%20employees%20while%20maintaining%20harmony%20between%20bots%20and%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20something%20Lattice%20CEO%20Sarah%20Franklin%20has%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20thinking%20about.%20Her%20company%2C%20which%20builds%20HR%20software%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flattice.com%2Fblog%2Fleading-the-way-in-responsible-ai-employment%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20year%20that%20it%20was%20going%20to%20treat%20AI%20workers%20like%20humans%20by%20giving%20them%20official%20employee%20records%20and%20even%20putting%20them%20through%20onboarding%20like%20a%20real%20human%20employee.%20The%20actual%20humans%20weren't%20keen%20on%20the%20idea%20and%20Lattice%20hit%20pause%20after%20the%20backlash.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-leaders-bill-gates-amazon-cto-share-2025-predictions-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etalk%20of%20AI%20agents%20everywhere%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Franklin%20says%20Lattice's%20idea%20was%20%26quot%3Breally%20prescient%26quot%3B%20if%20too%20early.%20%26quot%3BWe%20were%20ahead%2C%20but%20by%20months.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20prove%20to%20be%20so.%20Agentic%20AI%20is%20a%20hot%20topic%20at%20Davos%20this%20year.%20The%20past%20two%20years%20have%20brought%20much%20hype%20around%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20but%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20that%20can%20act%20and%20make%20decisions%20independent%20of%20user%20input%20%E2%80%94%20are%20what%20many%20stakeholders%20believe%20can%20provide%20tangible%2C%20immediate%20benefits.%20Or%2C%20as%20one%20exec%20in%20Davos%20put%20it%2C%20the%20time%20for%20kicking%20the%20tires%20is%20over.%20Businesses%20want%20returns%20on%20their%20investments%20%E2%80%94%20and%20agents%20are%20one%20way%20to%20get%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFranklin%20is%20not%20the%20only%20one%20raising%20the%20flag%20on%20this%20topic.%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20the%20world%20has%20yet%20had%20the%20opportunity%20to%20think%20through%20all%20of%20the%20implications%2C%26quot%3B%20Alan%20Flower%2C%20global%20head%20of%20AI%20at%20HCLTech%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20example%2C%20as%20a%20manager%2C%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20managing%20a%20human%20workforce%20and%20an%20agentic%20workforce%20at%20the%20same%20time%20%E2%80%94%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20to%20collaborate%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Flower.%20%26quot%3BMy%20agents%20are%20going%20to%20have%20to%20collaborate%20with%20agents%20from%20another%20company%2C%20for%20example.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20then%2C%20said%20Flower%2C%20is%20how%20do%20employers%20%26quot%3Bbroker%26quot%3B%20collaboration%20between%20agents%20%E2%80%94%20including%20from%20other%20companies%20%E2%80%94and%20motivate%20them%20to%20do%20good%20work%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWill%20we%20get%20to%20a%20phase%20where%20agentic%20AI%20will%20be%20given%20KPIs%3F%20These%20are%20all%20considerations%20that%20the%20world%20of%20work%20is%20going%20to%20have%20to%20kind%20of%20contemplate%2C%26quot%3B%20Flower%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20key%20performance%20indicators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b6f17a68-b0ba-44a9-8d59-e88600423e19%5C%22%3E'How%20do%20I%20manage%20them%3F'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFranklin%20says%20one%20of%20the%20mistakes%20Lattice%20made%20with%20its%20announcement%20last%20year%20was%20in%20how%20it%20communicated%20it.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20more%20comfortable%20with%20the%20word%20'agent'%20than%20they%20are%20with%20'digital%20worker%2C'%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20Franklin%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20huge%20lack%20of%20education%20of%20what%20AI%20is%20and%20a%20disbelief%20that%20AI%20is%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20have%20the%20types%20of%20conversations%20that%20it%20can.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20a%20huge%20opportunity%20for%20HR%20leaders%2C%20Franklin%20said.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20for%20Lattice%2C%20which%20counts%20OpenAI%2C%20Perplexity%2C%20and%20Anthropic%20among%20its%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecky%20Frankiewicz%2C%20chief%20commercial%20officer%20at%20ManpowerGroup%2C%20told%20BI%20she%20has%20been%20hearing%20a%20lot%20of%20talk%20about%20whether%20companies%20will%20need%20%26quot%3BAI%20managers%26quot%3B%20for%20their%20AI%20agents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20the%20first%20step%20in%20working%20out%20how%20to%20manage%20these%20AI%20employees%20is%2C%20how%20do%20I%20deploy%20them%20and%20make%20them%20productive%3F%20And%20then%20step%20two%20is%2C%20how%20do%20I%20manage%20them%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrankiewicz%20said%20she%20knew%20one%20consulting%20company%20already%20grappling%20with%20this.%20%26quot%3BThey've%20done%20the%20agents%20already%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20next%20question%20they%20were%20asking%20was%3A%20do%20we%20need%20to%20have%20managers%20for%20the%20agents%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELattice's%20Franklin%20thinks%20the%20discussion%20around%20AI%20in%20the%20workplace%20isn't%20being%20taken%20seriously%20enough%20%E2%80%94%20and%20needs%20to%20happen%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20reality%20is%20that%20today%2C%20AI%20is%20being%20implemented%20as%20agents%20to%20have%20conversations%20on%20behalf%20of%20brands%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20Franklin%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it's%20a%20huge%20amount%20of%20trust%20to%20put%20into%20AI%20without%20proper%20governance.%20As%20agents%20take%20on%20more%20responsibilities%2C%20more%20governance%20will%20be%20needed%20%E2%80%94%20but%20that%20means%20acknowledging%20the%20new%20reality%20and%20ha